{"parse":{"title":"The Red Sari","pageid":45092336,"revid":827068903,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption style=\"font-style:italic;padding-bottom:0.2em;\">The Red Sari <span class=\"Z3988\" title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Red+Sari&amp;rft.author=%5B%5BJavier+Moro%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=2015+January&amp;rft.pub=Roli+Books&amp;rft.pages=429\"></span></caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:The_Red_Sari.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"The Red Sari.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f1/The_Red_Sari.jpg/220px-The_Red_Sari.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"347\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f1/The_Red_Sari.jpg 1.5x\" data-file-width=\"251\" data-file-height=\"396\" /></a><div>A Dramatized Biography of Sonia Gandhi</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Author</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Javier_Moro\" title=\"Javier Moro\">Javier Moro</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Original&#160;title</th><td>\n<i>El sari rojo</i></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Translator</th><td>\nPeter J Hearn</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Country</th><td>\nSpain</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Language</th><td>\nEnglish</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Genre</th><td>\nNovel</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Publisher</th><td>\nRoli Books</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Publication date</div></th><td>\n2015 January</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Pages</th><td>\n429</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-93-5194-103-3\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-93-5194-103-3\">978-93-5194-103-3</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>The Red Sari</b></i> (El sari rojo), which is a dramatized version of Sonia Gandhi's life, ran into some controversy in India.<sup id=\"cite_ref-10qs_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10qs-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-IE_latest_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-IE_latest-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/wiki/Javier_Moro\" title=\"Javier Moro\">Javier Moro</a>'s Spanish and Italian publishers received emails from <a href=\"/wiki/Indian_National_Congress\" title=\"Indian National Congress\">Indian National Congress</a> lawyers and spokesperson <a href=\"/wiki/Abhishek_Singhvi\" title=\"Abhishek Singhvi\">Abhishek Singhvi</a> with demands to withdraw the book from stores. Singhvi stated that book distorted facts and misinterpreted details.<sup id=\"cite_ref-IE_latest_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-IE_latest-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>  The author always denied that the book is malicious.<sup id=\"cite_ref-10qs_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10qs-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The book was originally published in October 2008 in Spain<sup id=\"cite_ref-sari1_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sari1-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> in <a href=\"/wiki/Spanish_language\" title=\"Spanish language\">Spanish</a>. The book tells the story of the Gandhi family through the eyes of <a href=\"/wiki/Sonia_Gandhi\" title=\"Sonia Gandhi\">Sonia Gandhi</a>. Abhishek Singhvi claimed that the book violated a person's privacy for monetary gain.<sup id=\"cite_ref-sari3_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sari3-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> The book was finally released in India in January 2015 and was greeted with a big success.<sup id=\"cite_ref-RedSariNowOut_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-RedSariNowOut-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Red_Sari&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-10qs-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-10qs_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-10qs_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Reddy, Sheela (12 July 2010). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.outlookindia.com/article.aspx?266086\">\"10 Questions: Javier Moro\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Outlook_India\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Outlook India\">Outlook India</a></i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">20 February</span> 2014</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Outlook+India&amp;rft.atitle=10+Questions%3A+Javier+Moro&amp;rft.date=2010-07-12&amp;rft.aulast=Reddy&amp;rft.aufirst=Sheela&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.outlookindia.com%2Farticle.aspx%3F266086&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Red+Sari\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-IE_latest-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-IE_latest_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-IE_latest_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Charmy Harikrishnan (2 June 2010). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://indianexpress.com/article/news-archive/web/latest-target-for-congress-censors-book-on-sonias-life/99/\">\"Latest target for Congress censors: book on Sonia's life\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Indian_Express\" title=\"The Indian Express\">The Indian Express</a></i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrie